If the y-coordinate can be described by the equation [`g(x) = x/`][`[$coefficient]`] [` + 1`] and the cup has constant
density [`\rho = `] [`[$rho]`] [`kg/m^3`], determine its radius of gyration about the x-axis. The cone has dimensions 
[`h = `] [`[$h]`] [`m`] and [`l = `] [`[$l]`] [`m`].
  
[`k_x = `] [____]{"$k"} [`m`]  

END_PGML

